  "id": "3e748923a47dfa85",
  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/snowflake/936c2f42-1fd5-419a-b781-272df9f3f1dd/application",
    "company": "Snowflake",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "3e748923a47dfa85",
    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nSnowflake is at the forefront of the data and AI revolution - with a mission to help every company achieve its potential with data \u0026 AI. As part of our mission to enable every organization to achieve its full potential, the Snowflake Marketplace https://www.snowflake.com/en/product/features/marketplace/snowflake-marketplace-for-providers/ serves as the vibrant hub which enables customers to do more with data. We are building a platform that empowers organizations to seamlessly discover, access, and build with valuable datasets, cutting-edge applications, and intelligent AI agents.\n\nWith rapid growth of Snowflake Marketplace, we are not just adding new features - we are rethinking the architecture and reimagining the user experience to build a best-in-class product that scales to meet the demands of our global customer and partner ecosystem.\n\nWe are seeking a Software Engineering Manager who is a hands-on technical leader to guide a team of talented engineers in this critical area. You will manage a team responsible for full-stack development, partner closely with Product Management and Design to define the roadmap and drive execution, acting as a force multiplier for the team.\n\n\nAS A SOFTWARE ENGINEERING MANAGER AT SNOWFLAKE, YOU WILL:\n\n - Build and Grow a High-Performing Team: Manage, mentor, and grow a full stack team of 5–10 engineers. You will be responsible for hiring top talent, managing performance, and fostering a culture of technical excellence, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\n - Drive Cross-Functional Impact: Partner tightly with Product Managers and UX Designers to understand \u0026 translate customer needs into robust technical solutions. You will play a key role in shaping the product roadmap and ensuring the team creates intuitive, seamless user experiences.\n\n - Lead Technical Strategy, Execution \u0026 Delivery: Actively participate in design reviews, technical decision-making, and oversee the end-to-end software development lifecycle. Ensure the team delivers on time with high quality, balancing speed of delivery with long-term architectural health and scalability.\n\n - Elevate Engineering Culture: Champion engineering operational excellence. You will refine agile processes, improve developer velocity, and ensure the team adheres to high standards for testing, monitoring, and documentation.\n\n\nOUR IDEAL SOFTWARE ENGINEERING MANAGER WILL HAVE:\n\n - Engineering Management Experience: 3+ years of experience managing high-performing full stack engineering teams (ideally 5–10 engineers), with a proven track record of hiring, coaching, and retaining top talent.\n\n - Strong Technical Depth: 10+ years of total software engineering experience with a strong background in leading full-stack development. You should have previous experience as a senior/staff engineer and be capable of diving into code and architecture discussions when necessary.\n\n - Cross-Functional Collaboration: Demonstrated ability to work effectively with Product Management and User Experience (UX) teams to build complex, customer-facing products.\n\n - Technical Fluency: Familiarity with the modern stack used by the team, including TypeScript, React, and languages like Java, Python and Go.\n\n - Operational Excellence: Experience managing project scope, setting clear goals, and guiding complex projects from concept to launch in a fast-paced environment.\n\n - Product Passion: A genuine passion for creating exceptional user experiences and a relentless drive to deliver measurable value to customers and partners.\n\nEvery Snowflake employee is expected to follow the company’s confidentiality and security standards for handling sensitive data. Snowflake employees must abide by the company’s data security plan as an essential part of their duties. It is every employee's duty to keep customer information secure and confidential.\n\nThe following represents the expected range of compensation for this role:\n\n - The estimated base salary range for this role is $236,000 - $339,200.\n\n - Additionally, this role is eligible to participate in Snowflake’s bonus and equity plan.\n\nThe successful candidate’s starting salary will be determined based on permissible, non-discriminatory factors such as skills, experience, and geographic location. This role is also eligible for a competitive benefits https://careers.snowflake.com/us/en/benefits package that includes: medical, dental, vision, life, and disability insurance; 401(k) retirement plan; flexible spending \u0026 health savings account; at least 12 paid holidays; paid time off; parental leave; employee assistance program; and other company benefits.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
